Preheat the oven to 170C/150C Fan/Gas 3.Put the pork in an ovenproof dish with the stock, bay leaves and peppercorns. Cook for 2–3 hours, or until very tender.Strain the juices and discard. Shred the meat using two forks, discarding any large bits of fat. Put the shredded pork in a bowl with 25g/1oz of the butter, the paprika, honey and soy sauce and leave to marinate.Bring a large pan of salted water to the boil and cook the potatoes for 10–12 minutes, or until tender. Drain and return to the pan. Mash with the remaining butter, the cream, garlic, cheese and parsley.Mix together the pork and the potato, season with salt and pepper and chill for at least 1 hour.Put the flour, egg and breadcrumbs into three separate bowls. Line a baking tray with baking paper.Divide the potato mixture into 12. Use your hands to shape the potato mixture into small barrel-shaped croquettes. Roll each croquette in the flour, then the egg, then the breadcrumbs. Place on the baking tray until ready to fry.Heat a deep-fat fryer to 180C, or when a cube of bread browns in 20 seconds (CAUTION: hot oil can be dangerous. Do not leave unattended.).Fry the croquettes in batches for 2–3 minutes, or until golden brown.Sprinkle with sea salt and serve immediately.